JOHANNESBURG &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s rand firmed more than one percent against the dollar on Monday as the greenback pulled back after hitting a 13 1/2-year high against a basket of currencies.At 0852 GMT, the rand traded at 14.2650 per dollar, 1.42% firmer from its New York close on Friday.The dollar index, which tracks the US unit against a basket of six rivals, fell 0.26% to 100.95 after notching a high of 101.48 on Friday, its highest since April 2003.